Alberta is one of the thirteen provinces and territories of Canada. 

It is part of Western Canada and is one of the three prairie provinces.

Alberta is bordered by British Columbia to the west, Saskatchewan to the east, the Northwest Territories (NWT) to the north, and the U.S. state of Montana to the south.

Alberta is the 4th largest province by area at 661,848 km2 and the 4th most populous, being home to 4,262,635 people.
